.TH RIND-SYSINVOKE 1 "2026-06-07" "rind" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
rind-sysinvoke \- send arbitrary IPC actions to the daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rind sysinvoke
.I name
.I payload
.RB [ \-\-scope
.IR scope ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B rind sysinvoke
sends a raw IPC message to a named endpoint in the daemon. The
.I payload
is a JSON string or arbitrary data that is forwarded to the target runtime or handler.
.PP
This is a low-level command for sending custom actions that do not have dedicated CLI subcommands. Use with caution.
.PP
When invoked as
.B sysinvoke
(directly), the same arguments apply.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I name
The target endpoint name (e.g., a runtime action name).
.TP
.I payload
The payload to send. If valid JSON, it is sent as-is. Otherwise, it is wrapped as a string value.
.TP
.BI \-\-scope " scope"
Target scope namespace. If specified and not
.IR static ,
the
.I name
field in JSON payloads is automatically scoped.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
rind sysinvoke my_action '{"key": "value"}'
rind sysinvoke custom_handler "plain data" \-\-scope myscope
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR rind (1),
.BR rind-sysman (1)
